      "problem": "Let $N$ be the number of ordered pairs of nonempty sets $\\mathcal{A}$ and $\\mathcal{B}$ that partition $\{1, 2, \\dots, 11\}$ such that $|\\mathcal{A}| \\notin \\mathcal{A}$, $|\\mathcal{B}| \\notin \\mathcal{B}$, and $|\\mathcal{A}|$ is a multiple of 3. Find $N$.",
